result.execSummary:
The defendant Christopher L. Dworshak was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Christopher L. Dworshak is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Christopher L. Dworshak was found guilty of Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Sean Edward Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin. 16CF36, 16CF120, 16CT76, and 16TR1004-1005 heard at this time. Remaining counts and case to be dismissed. probation on 16CF148 and 16CF36; successful completion of Pierce County Drug Court program.  16CT76: $1429 fine, 12 month revocation of DL, AODA, IID and 16 days jail. 169 days credit on 16CF148, 75 days credit on 16CF36 and 16CT76.
